# Documentation Standard

Documentation is a first-class deliverable. Never stop after writing code alone.

## Canonical Location

All project docs live under `docs/`:

```
docs/
  ROADMAP.md
  PROJECT_MEMORY.md
  CHANGELOG.md
  ARCHITECTURE.md
  architecture/          # ADRs
    ADR-001-*.md
    ...
```

Root `README.md` is the public entry point; it links to `docs/`.

## Mandatory Workflow

1. Review existing implementation and docs.
2. Implement the change.
3. Update documentation in the **same task**.
4. Summarize what changed and why.

## Per-File Update Rules

### `docs/PROJECT_MEMORY.md` — always update

Append a dated entry with: phase, objective, files changed, decisions, remaining work, next task. Never delete history.

### `docs/CHANGELOG.md` — always update

Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/). Use `Added`, `Changed`, `Fixed`, `Removed` sections under `## [Unreleased]` or dated headings.

### `docs/ROADMAP.md` — update when

- A phase or sub-phase is completed
- Current phase changes
- New phases or milestones are added

Do not rewrite completed history.

### `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — update when

- Folder structure, request flow, or service boundaries change
- Database design or provider architecture changes
- New middleware, routing, or integration points are added

Keep Mermaid diagrams current.

### ADRs — create when

A significant architectural decision is made (technology choice, pattern adoption, boundary change).

Location: `docs/architecture/ADR-NNN-short-title.md`

Required sections: Status, Context, Decision, Consequences, Alternatives Considered.

## Pre-Finish Checklist

- [ ] Code compiles / imports cleanly
- [ ] PROJECT_MEMORY updated
- [ ] CHANGELOG updated
- [ ] ROADMAP updated (if phase changed)
- [ ] ARCHITECTURE updated (if structure changed)
- [ ] ADR created (if decision made)

If documentation is missing, the task is **not complete**.
